III. We now come to the consideration of those words, the quantity of which, as used by Plautus, differs from that observed by later writers. Considering that quantity depends upon pronunciation, we might have expected to find a number of words, the pronunciation, and therefore the quantity, of which had undergone a change during the 150 years which elapsed from the period when Plautus ssourishcd to the last days of the Republic. But these are in fact very few.
